  "prompt": "What is the best way to substitute celery seeds in a recipe?",
  "response": "If you need to substitute celery seeds in a recipe, there are several options depending on the flavor profile you're aiming for and the availability of ingredients. Here are some good alternatives:\n\n### 1. **Celery Salt**  \n   - Use 1 teaspoon of celery salt to replace 1/2 teaspoon of celery seeds, but reduce the amount of added salt in the recipe to avoid over-salting.\n\n### 2. **Fresh Celery**  \n   - Chopped fresh celery (especially the leaves) can provide a similar flavor. Use about 1/4 cup of finely chopped celery for every 1 teaspoon of celery seeds.\n\n### 3. **Fennel Seeds**  \n   - Fennel seeds have a slightly licorice-like flavor but can mimic the earthiness of celery seeds. Use an equal amount of fennel seeds as a substitute.\n\n### 4. **Dill Seeds**  \n   - Dill seeds offer a grassy, slightly tangy flavor that can work in savory dishes. Use an equal amount of dill seeds as a substitute.\n\n### 5. **Caraway Seeds**  \n   - Caraway seeds have a nutty, earthy flavor that can work as a substitute. Use half the amount of caraway seeds since they can be more intense.\n\n### 6. **Parsley and Celery Leaves**  \n   - A combination of fresh parsley and celery leaves can provide a fresh, herbal flavor similar to celery seeds.\n\nChoose the substitute based on the dish and the flavor you\u2019re trying to achieve!",
